Some questioning the value of inflation swaps (driven mainly by crude prices) as a guide to coming Fed policy.  But, it is hard to ignore that the current repricing from cuts to hikes was concurrent with the surge in Oil prices.  So a retreat has to have some impact on the Fed's policy decisions but admittedly not exclusively as the labor market has strengthened in that timeframe as well.

@BlacklionCTA I could have made my arguments with just crude prices in this case.  But to your point, short term inflation swaps were very useful to me during the tariff surge, especially the 1-year 1-year forward swap

They do what they are supposed to do well.   Good indication of what headline inflation will be in the next year.  Of course, the biggest day to day driver is crude which may or may not be a concern to the Fed.   At times Fed may ignore crude prices for a variety of reasons and in those instances, swaps probably will not offer much insight

